Image title080809-N-0773H-050 BALTIMORE, MD (August 9, 2008) Members of the USS Sterett await the command to "board the ship and bring it to life" during the Commissioning Ceremony for the USS Sterett at the at South Locust Point Marine Terminal in Baltimore, Md., the fourth ship to bear this name. Lt. Andrew Sterett, a native of Baltimore, served in the West Indies and the Mediterranean Sea in the late 1790s and early 1800s.

U.S. Navy Photo by MUC Stephen Hassay
